result.execSummary:
The defendant Donna M Baldwin was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-Expose Genitals/Pubic Area/Intimate Parts, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(3).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Computer Message-Threaten/Obscenity, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.0125(2)(c).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court reviews collateral consequences, possible penalties if defendant should be convicted of a felony.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Cts. 2 & 3. Court withholds accepting of the plea on Ct. 1 to allow defendant the opportunity to complete terms of the Deferred Acceptance of Guilty Plea Agreement. Court dismisses Ct. 4 but reads in for sentencing. Court reviews DAGPA with defendant, approves and signs agreement. Upon successful completion of DAGPA, State will, after 2 years, move to dismiss Ct. 1, which can be done by written stipulation. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Defendant apologizes to the court. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond remains in effect regarding Ct. 1.
